.TH "snd_dmaengine_pcm_prepare_slave_config" 9 "snd_dmaengine_pcm_prepare_slave_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_dmaengine_pcm_prepare_slave_config \- Generic prepare_slave_config callback
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_dmaengine_pcm_prepare_slave_config
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_hw_params *params "  ","
.BI "struct dma_slave_config *slave_config "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
PCM substream
.IP "params" 12
hw_params
.IP "slave_config" 12
DMA slave config to prepare
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function can be used as a generic prepare_slave_config callback for
platforms which make use of the snd_dmaengine_dai_dma_data struct for their
DAI DMA data. Internally the function will first call
snd_hwparams_to_dma_slave_config to fill in the slave config based on the
hw_params, followed by snd_dmaengine_set_config_from_dai_data to fill in the
remaining fields based on the DAI DMA data.
